---
/**
 * SEO content section component
 *
 * Provides informative content for SEO and user guidance.
 * Explains how the tool works and lists key features.
 *
 * @component
 */
---

<section class="mt-16 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">How It Works</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        This tool parses your SVG file and extracts all embedded images including PNG, JPEG, GIF, and WebP formats.
        Simply upload your SVG file, import from a URL, or paste the SVG code, and download all images with one click.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Features</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Extract base64-encoded images from SVG files</li>
        <li>Support for PNG, JPEG, GIF, WebP formats</li>
        <li>Import from file upload, URL, or paste SVG code</li>
        <li>Download all images as ZIP file</li>
        <li>100% client-side - your files never leave your browser</li>
        <li>Free and unlimited usage</li>
        <li>No registration required</li>
    </ul>
</section>
